:<div>

nod /nɒd/

(nodding,nodded,nods) 

1. V-T/V-I If you nod , you move your head downward and upward to show that you are answering 'yes' to a question, or to show agreement, understanding, or approval. 点头 [no passive] 

例： 'Are you okay?' I asked. She nodded and smiled. “你还好吧？”我问道。她点点头笑了。 

例： Jacques tasted one and nodded his approval. 雅克品尝了一个并点头表示赞许。 

2. N-COUNT Nod is also a noun. 点头 

例： She gave a nod and said, 'I see.' 她点了一下头说：“我明白了。” 

例： 'Probably,' agreed Hunter, with a slow nod of his head. “可能，”亨特慢慢点了一下头赞同地说道。 

3. V-I If you nod in a particular direction, you bend your head once in that direction in order to indicate something or to give someone a signal. (朝某方向) 点头示意 [no passive] 

例： 'Does it work?' he asked, nodding at the piano. “它能弹吗？”他问道，点头指向那架钢琴。 

例： She nodded toward the dining room. 'He's in there.' 她朝餐厅点了点头说：“他在那里面。” 

4. V-T/V-I If you nod , you bend your head once, as a way of saying hello or goodbye. 点头 (以示打招呼或告别) [no passive] 

例： All the girls nodded and said 'Hi.' 所有女孩们都点头说:“你好。” 

例： Both of them smiled and nodded at friends. 他们两个都微笑着朝朋友们点了点头。 

例： Tom nodded a greeting. 汤姆点头打了个招呼。

